<worksheet >
    <title>TF-4 Laws of Sines and Cosines</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>Complete both parts to get M. Complete part a with progress on part b to get P.</p>
  </introduction>
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="2.5in">
      <introduction><p>Three forest fire lookout towers are positioned such that Tower B 
        is 15 miles away from Tower A, and Tower C is 25 miles away from Tower A. Tower C 
        is exactly 20 miles away from Tower B. Tower B is located due north of Tower A.</p></introduction>
        <task><statement><p>Draw a diagram to model this situation.</p></statement></task>
        <task><statement><p>Find the bearing from Tower A to Tower C. Give a simplified 
          expression for your answer.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>